
[1]fully

   FUL'LY, adv.

   1. Completely; entirely; without lack or defect; in a manner to give
   satisfaction; to the extent desired; as, to be fully persuaded of the
   truth of a proposition.

   2. Completely; perfectly. Things partially known in this life will be
   hereafter fully disclosed.
